title: Carved Wood Panel, 1972-79-2, early 20th century
description: Three carved openwork teak panels with two matching side panels and unique center panel. Side panels are made up of openwork serpentine floral motifts contained within a frame toped with a pointed arch, then surrounded by carved frames made up of sinous vine motifs; top portion is a lighter color wood with framed rosettes. Center panel has carved openwork with serpentine floral motifts contained within a frame topped with a pointed arch and surrounded by frame of sinous vines that takes up the entire height of the piece.
